# Architecture Rules

## 1. Layered Architecture (Mandatory)

The system MUST follow a strict layered architecture:

Frontend:

* UI (View)
* State / Store
* API Client

Backend:

* Router (API Layer)
* Service (Business Logic)
* Repository (Data Access)

---

## 2. Separation of Concerns

Each layer MUST have a single responsibility:

* UI: rendering and user interaction ONLY
* Service: business logic ONLY
* Repository: data access ONLY

Cross-layer logic is strictly forbidden.

---

## 3. Data Flow

Frontend:
UI → API Client → Backend

Backend:
Router → Service → Repository

Reverse calls are NOT allowed.

---

## 4. No Business Logic in Controllers

* Frontend components MUST NOT contain business logic
* Backend routers MUST NOT contain business logic

---

## 5. Stateless Design (Default)

* Services should be stateless unless explicitly required
* Avoid hidden shared state

---

## 6. Extensibility First

* New services (e.g. WITHDRAW, DEPOSIT) must be addable without modifying existing logic
* Prefer configuration (metadata, templates) over hardcoding

---

## 7. Fail Fast

* Validate inputs at the boundary (API layer)
* Throw explicit errors
